    "narrative": "The Austin Waves offense faces a favorable slate today, anchored by **Gunnar Henderson**, whose 81.88 efficiency score makes him our most potent asset. With a soft matchup against Lugo and a helpful wind pushing balls out of the park, **Gunnar Henderson** is poised to anchor our run production, particularly with his elite stolen base potential remaining the engine of our strategy. Following closely is **Andy Pages** (74.43), who benefits from a high-ceiling encounter with Quintana; the park factor combined with an advantageous platoon situation makes him a mandatory start. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (73.66) and **Drake Baldwin** (71.27) also round out our top tier, both benefiting significantly from favorable opposing pitcher xERAs that suggest we can exploit high-volume scoring opportunities against Elder and J. Irvin, respectively.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Nolan Schanuel**, who posted a 46.58 score. While he remains a steady contact-oriented floor play, he was squeezed out of the starting nine by the superior daily efficiency scores of **Dominic Smith** and **Josh Lowe**. **Josh Lowe**, despite facing the tougher arm in Cease, maintains a higher upside for category production that justifies the risk. We are monitoring **Jacob Wilson** and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** closely, as their scores are based on projected lineup slots. Should either drop down in their respective orders, we may see a minor dip in their output, though both are currently secure in the lineup. Note that **Kyle Tucker**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, and **Jackson Merrill** are unavailable today due to schedule gaps or rest, limiting our ability to rotate in high-end speed threats should the game states shift.",
